of true natural scientists and amplified with many important remarks.
Berlin and Leipzig, Publisher Geroge Jacob Decker, 1781.”
The preface, signed “Phlebochron” is followed by the “listing of the
chapters” and it is preceded by 1) an illustration plus a poetic
“explanation of the figure Abyssi Duplicatae or the twice volatile and
fixed abyss”; 2) an illustration of the catena (see cover) plus poetic
“explanation of the Annuli Platonis or the golden chain of Homer”; 3)
a “remarks.”
We do not show a copy of the two “Carmina” here, because even
though they Contain nothing different than the book itself, it would
