natural world. The interior world and the outside world exist not only
each separately, but also each connected to the other in an orderly
fashion, and in a bilateral connection, since they are basically only one
world. Nothing can be recognised in an isolated form, but each thing
only should be seen within its connection and its relation with other
things. Lassalle once formulated this very accurately:
“It is one of the most profound philosophical ideas ever expressed, that
nothing is known for itself, but everything is known only within its organic
relation with its ‘wherefrom’ and ‘whereto’ in the natural and spiritual
universe, i.e., it may be understood only in relation with the whole or
absolute true.”
