 additional material for restoration. The work of R.A.M.S. Includes such material as “Last Will and Testament” of Basil Valentine, important selections from the invaluable Bacstrom Manuscripts such as “Golden Chain of Homer”, “Lamspring’ a Process for the Lapis Sophorum”, “The Chemist’ a Key”, “The Mineral Gluten of Nitre and Sulphur”, “Coelum Philosophorum” and others. Additionally, material by other writers is or will be offered. Such as Geber, Khalid, Ripley, Bacon, Hazelrigg, etc. It is highly appropriate to acknowledge the many persons who have either materially or philosophically contributed to the present effort and future ones. For some, this might well be the first indication that they are considered as members of R.A.M.S. or that such a group even exists! While the list is long, it includes: C. Collins, Rick Stern, Doris Edlein, Arp. Joo, D. and J. Nintzel, N. Ogle, G. Price, F. Regardie, W. van Doren, K. von Koenigseck and especially David Ham. For their labours and contributions, grateful thanks are given. Let their unselfish efforts inspire others to light the fires of Alchemy. Hans W. Nintzel ALCHEMICAL SYMBOLS The symbols used in this edition are faithfully reproduced from original editions as well as from R.A.M.S. edition translation, mostly drawn by Br. Moreh and few by me: symbol    󰀄 description Acidum, acid, vinegar Air element, air Amalgam Ana – (from Latin) is used to indicate equal parts of each of the substances named - means "of each" or "equal parts of the following substances."   Antimony 🝾 Aqua Regia, spirit of aqua regia  🝎󰀅 🜓 ♀ 🝰    ☉O Bain Marie – water bath Aqua Fortis Caput Mortuum, “dead head” Cinnabar Copper, Venus Day/night Dram (apothecary) = 3 scruples = 3,888g Earth element, earth, Salt Fire element, fire Gold, sun, ovum/egg symbol  ♂ ♄ ☿   󰀂   🝋  ♆ 🜀 󰀁    ☽  description Hour Iron, Mars Lead, Saturn Mercury principle, quicksilver Month Nitre Nota Bene (Latin) – Note well, pay attention Oil, essence  Ounce (a